Description: Us Patent Commission utilizes a simple, two-step program that comes with a professionally prepared provisional patent application.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Since March 16, 2013 the America Invents Act changed the rules for determining ownership of an invention idea. Before this date, when two inventors that disputed ownership of an invention, the law favored the inventor who could prove they first conceived of the idea. Now, even if an inventor has worked on an idea for years - with the evidence to prove they first conceived of the idea and reduced it to practice - if someone else files a patent application first, the prior inventor has no rights. In short, the test of ownership is simple...Who filed first. So for inventors the advice is simple. File your application as soon as possible or risk losing your idea.

Description: Bar directory for your favorite team.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: What is BarChannels? This website is a directory of bars & pubs where sports fans can search for the best local places to watch their teams. The Back-Story Necessity is the mother of invention. Co-founders Tom O'Malley & Don Lavis began building BarChannels after countless frustrating occasions of needing such a resource. Every week seemed to present the same question: How can a couple of rowdy, high-fiving gentlemen find a bar that is filled with our team's fans and playing our team's games? You can't! Well... you couldn't. But now you can! There are many wonderful websites, apps & guides out there to help people discover bars in their city. A simple search of these resources will conclude that almost all sports bars play a wide range of games. However, many do favor a handful of specific teams and those places truly are your best chances for a great time! BarChannels.com was created to bring like-minded sports fans together at the best places to watch their favorite teams. The 5 Commandments May we never stray from our founding principles: 1. All bar listings shall be kept accurate and up-to-date by our editors. 2. Reviews & ratings shall be informative, helpful and un-biased. 3. This site shall never be overrun with ads, pop-ups or promotions. 4. Simplicity is key, while maintaining sexy aesthetic standards. 5. Push to exceed expectations with fresh content & new features.

Full Description: When families and their loved ones need assistance, it’s critical to choose a health services agency that can offer high quality, compassionate care. DaVinci is here to help reduce the stress and anxiety that can occur during these times, and create greater peace of mind for both the individuals in our care and their families. Whatever your family’s needs are, whether it’s for one hour of 24, seven days a week, we can help – any time. Our highly skilled care professionals provide care to anyone , wherever they need it; services tailored to a loved one’s needs. Our personal care services include personal hygiene care like bath visits and grooming, home safety evaluations to prevent unnecessary accidents, outpatient support to ease stress before and after surgical procedures as well as medication reminders to stay on track with prescription doses. Our client relations staff can quickly report a patients' status to their primary care provider. We plan to  offer highly skilled services; nursing for  neurological care, blood sugar testing, home infusion therapy, hospice assistance, respite care,  services for people with disabilities, dementia, and/or special needs, as well as physical,  occupational, and speech therapy.  We are here to make life less complicated for families and their loved ones. We strive to make more possible in the lives of the individuals we care for. Each client receives a personal, in-depth assessment conducted by our qualified in-home support staff that takes into account their condition, personality and environment. We then put that knowledge to use, creating an individualized plan of care that meets our clients’ unique physical and emotional needs. A plan that strives to not only improve their health, but enhance their quality of life. This process helps us ensure the right fit between our clients and their caregivers, and enables us to quickly modify a client’s plan of care as their needs evolve. Description: Estate Planning - Probate, Trusts, Wills, Business Law - Business Litigation, Business Planning, Contract Disputes in Bloomfield Twp, MI
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Running a business is a hard thing to do, even when it is your passion.  There is always a need for legal advice when it comes to running any business, but most companies are far too small to support a legal department of their own.  That’s why Kendal Law Group PC exists.  We offer legal solutions to business owners. Corporate business lawyers aren’t always the easiest to work with, but we’re proud to say that we stand out from the rest in that regard.  We want to ensure that our clients are able to solve their legal issues and achieve their objectives in a timely and cost-effective manner. However, we also understand that business law brushes up against several other areas. One example is commercial litigation, and we offer comprehensive services in that regard.  Estate planning seems like such a personal matter, and it is, but that doesn’t mean it is entirely separate from your business.  As the owner of the business, there is a very real chance that debts the company owns will fall to you.  Should you pass before getting your estate in order then those same debts could be forwarded onto your loved ones.  Rather than leave them trying to deal with managing all your leftover debts or going through an annoying and lengthy probate process, why not get everything in order today to save them the pain and confusion?  Working with an estate planning attorney, such as those in Kendal Law Group, can even help you to secure your financial footing and protect your assets so that those previously mentioned debts don’t take you by surprise.  By considering estate planning from a business perspective, you can see just how important it is that you get started planning your estate today and stop waiting until it is too late.  Reach out to our law firm in Bloomfield Hills today to get started.

Full Description: TrueAutomation.io is a SaaS for testing automation professionals that solves the everlasting problem of locators in web testing. When using TrueAutomation.io, regular locators are substituted with a unique footprint of an element generated by our AI-based engine. This approach allows to avoid further maintenance of tests even when the page is changed dramatically and at the same time keeps the experience of writing tests the same as in regular Selenium environment. TrueAutomation.io also handles test coverage of technologies with dynamic DOM tree (e.g. React, GWT, Vaadin) without any additional coding and efforts.  Our mission is to make testing automation truly automatic by bringing AI to elements detection process. At the same time we believe that it is not right to make yet another product that requires product-specific knowledge, proprietary coding, etc. That's why TrueAutomation.io is compatible with regular Selenium environment so that testing professionals can create tests in the environment they are used to.

Description: Lucends is an e-commerce website that provides bags, clutches, pillow covers, and tote and travel cosmetic bags for consumers.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: lucends was created 5 years ago when my first born son died after open heart surgery. I need something to  keep my mind busy, having a love of color, texture and design, I taught myself how to sew. Lucends was born. Over the last 5 years my business has grown, I have gone from using other designers fabric, to creating my own designs and having them printed. These designs are exclusive to lucends. I am moving away from selling my work at art shows and into the wholesale arena. My work is currently sold in boutiques in New York, Pennsylvania and Florida.  I am currently in the process of creating a children's clothing line using my designs. It will be launching for pre-orders in the next two weeks. In addition, I am working with a a local handmade stationary maker and using my designs on her home office line of products. This line will be launching in the next month. Everything that I have made has gone back into the business. It has been cash in and cash out. The business does not have any debt. I am at a critical point in the life of the business that in order to continue to grow and expand I need some working capital. The retail consumer over the last few years has embraced handmade products. They want to support local independent artists, as well as products that are made in the USA. Yes my products are handmade and the designs are mine, but what draws people to my product is the story. Knowing  that they are a part of my healing  makes them feel connected to me and the  product they are purchasing.  I believe in my product. It is well made with great attention to detail., but I believe that story behind the product is what makes it stand out.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Consumer Goods, Design

Description: HomeBuzz, a crowdsourced mobile application, allows its members to search real estate for sale and check-in, review, or estimate the prices.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: How do you get from the current broken real estate model that all of the United States uses to transact real estate, and transform it into a mobile experience that allows collaboration and transparency throughout the entire process, and also saves consumers thousands of dollars and weeks of their time...  Answer: baby steps - take on a simple piece of the problem, make it an amazing experience, and add on from there. Enter HomeBuzz - a Yelp-like experience for homes. Allow real estate professionals to continue doing their job, compete for commissions, separate the weak from the strong, and allow consumers to benefit. Wouldn't you like to know who has seen a home that is for sale, what they thought about it, and how much they thought it would sell for? Better yet, when the home sells, rank each user according to who was closest to the actual sales price. View, in real time, who is commenting on what property, what they are saying, and how good they are at it. Next baby step - allow users to transact real estate from their mobile device, in real time. Submit an offer, chat with the seller or agent, receive a counter-offer, and work toward an accepted purchase contract, all done within minutes, instead of days. Next baby step - invite all parties involved in the transaction (lender, escrow agent, appraiser, title officer, home inspector, etc) into the conversation. Setup a to-do list for each party and a timeline. Monitor, in real time, who is responsible for what action, and when that action will be complete. Sign documents, complete addendums, review reports, revise terms, and close the transaction. All of this will be done from any device, from anywhere in the world. Next (not so) baby step - roll the platform out globally, and allow transactions anywhere in the world, completed in real-time. This works for rental properties too - San Francisco and NYC were looking at you first. HomeBuzz - What Real Estate Should Be!

Full Description: On April 3, 1963, Upper Cleveland Life Savers and Rescue Squad was chartered. The five members served as the first board of directors and they formed a corporation whose purpose was “to serve as a county and community rescue squad providing free emergency services, including ambulance and first aid service and any other emergency services the corporation is or may be equipped to render”. That was almost 60 years ago, and although many things have changed within the county and the organization, our mission remains much the same. The mission of Upper Cleveland Rescue Squad is to provide outstanding emergency medical services, public education, and emergency medical training to the citizens in the North end of Cleveland County and surrounding areas, in a professional manner while maintaining the dignity of those we serve. Our commitment to service implores us to provide quality pre-hospital care and life safety while treating individuals with illness and injury in our community with care and compassion, utilizing effective principles and practices of patient care, and we strive for excellence through ongoing evaluation and improvement. We will be responsive to the needs and priorities of our community and the residents we serve. We recognize the dignity of others and communicate with others in a respectful manner. We serve with honesty, loyalty, and dedication. We are responsible for our actions, both positive and negative, and we practice teamwork through communications and cooperation to achieve common goals. We shall not participate in unethical behaviors or procedures and shall assume the responsibility of exposing incompetence or unethical conduct of others to the appropriate authority in a proper and professional manner. We do not discriminate against patients on the basis of race, color, national origin, ancestry, religion, sex, age, disability, political belief, military service, sexual orientation or financial standing.
